1
00:00:06,506 --> 00:00:08,508
(Arisugawa) You kind of understand, right?

2
00:00:08,508 --> 00:00:10,510
Who is suitable for CURO?

3
00:00:10,510 --> 00:00:12,011
BEAT…｡

4
00:00:12,011 --> 00:00:14,013
(Kurosaki) I am not Mr. Arisugawa➡

5
00:00:14,013 --> 00:00:16,516
I've always been in love with another woman.

6
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:19,519
Choosing someone other than her➡

7
00:00:19,519 --> 00:00:21,521
There is no eternal future.

8
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:24,023
Koharu-san is trying not to worry others➡

9
00:00:24,023 --> 00:00:26,025
Trying to hold it alone.

10
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:30,029
I love your kindness.

11
00:00:30,029 --> 00:00:33,533
(Koharu) 《I have already done it➡

12
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:36,033
To Mr. Kurosaki...》

13
00:00:39,038 --> 00:00:41,040
(Mika) How about more?

14
00:00:41,040 --> 00:00:44,043
What does it feel like to fall in love for the first time?

15
00:00:44,043 --> 00:00:45,545
Hmm.

16
00:00:45,545 --> 00:00:48,548
It's embarrassing and itchy.

17
00:00:48,548 --> 00:00:52,051
I can't calm down. Kya~!

18
00:00:52,051 --> 00:00:54,554
It's new.

19
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:57,056
We're finally meeting each other.

20
00:00:57,056 --> 00:00:59,058
So when are you going to confess?

21
00:00:59,058 --> 00:01:02,562
(Riri) Valentine's Day is coming soon so it might be a good time.

22
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:04,497
keep company?

23
00:01:04,497 --> 00:01:06,499
Confession?

24
00:01:06,499 --> 00:01:10,503
You weren't thinking about that, were you?

25
00:01:10,503 --> 00:01:14,007
If you like Koharu, you're both in love with her, right?

26
00:01:14,007 --> 00:01:17,007
I didn't think about it at all...

27
00:01:18,511 --> 00:01:20,513
Love Master Mika-sama!

28
00:01:20,513 --> 00:01:24,013
What should I do about confession?

29
00:01:33,526 --> 00:01:36,529
(cheers) ⚟Amazing! ⚞

30
00:01:36,529 --> 00:01:38,529
The important thing is...

31
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:42,033
Passion!

32
00:01:43,036 --> 00:01:45,538
Kurosaki-san was like that too, right?

33
00:01:45,538 --> 00:01:50,043
All you have to do is just hit your burning love straight!

34
00:01:50,043 --> 00:01:52,045
I see.

35
00:01:52,045 --> 00:01:55,548
That's right, like Kurosaki-san.

36
00:01:55,548 --> 00:01:58,051
Let's go, Koharu!

37
00:01:58,051 --> 00:02:00,551
Kurosaki-san is waiting!

38
00:02:01,554 --> 00:02:03,454
Wow!

39
00:02:04,991 --> 00:02:07,491
Yay! a….

40
00:02:16,002 --> 00:02:17,502
Wow...!

41
00:02:21,007 --> 00:02:24,511
《Mika-chan and Riri-chan put so much thought into it➡

42
00:02:24,511 --> 00:02:29,015
Next time Kurosaki-san comes to the store, I'll definitely ask him out on a date! 》

43
00:02:29,015 --> 00:02:31,515
《Let's simulate it in your mind》

44
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:38,024
Kukukukukuku... Kurosaki-san, if you don't mind...

45
00:02:38,024 --> 00:02:41,027
Wow... I'm sorry!

46
00:02:41,027 --> 00:02:42,529
Ah... Kurosaki-san!?

47
00:02:42,529 --> 00:02:45,031
Koharu-san, are you okay?

48
00:02:45,031 --> 00:02:48,535
Ah... soooo... sorry... I was careless.

49
00:02:48,535 --> 00:02:51,035
Ah, no, it's me.

50
00:02:52,539 --> 00:02:55,041
《What should I do? It's now, right? 》

51
00:02:55,041 --> 00:02:58,044
《But I'm still not mentally prepared...》

52
00:02:58,044 --> 00:03:01,047
《Or rather...》

53
00:03:01,047 --> 00:03:03,483
《Well... it's dazzling! 》

54
00:03:03,483 --> 00:03:06,486
``She's more beautiful than ever...! 》

55
00:03:06,486 --> 00:03:08,488
Mr. Koharu?

56
00:03:08,488 --> 00:03:11,491
"no! Don't flinch, Koharu! 》

57
00:03:11,491 --> 00:03:13,993
``You decided to ask me out on a date! 》

58
00:03:13,993 --> 00:03:23,503
♬～

59
00:03:23,503 --> 00:03:25,505
Mr. Kurosaki!

60
00:03:25,505 --> 00:03:27,006
yes.

61
00:03:27,006 --> 00:03:29,509
Well, that...

62
00:03:29,509 --> 00:03:32,509
Ah... that's right...

63
00:03:37,016 --> 00:03:47,527
♬～

64
00:03:47,527 --> 00:03:49,529
sorry.

65
00:03:49,529 --> 00:03:53,032
My face was red so I thought I had a fever.

66
00:03:53,032 --> 00:03:55,535
No, no... no, no... it's okay!

67
00:03:55,535 --> 00:03:58,035
That would be fine.

68
00:04:02,976 --> 00:04:07,981
But... please don't push yourself when you're having a hard time.

69
00:04:07,981 --> 00:04:09,981
yes….

70
00:04:12,986 --> 00:04:15,488
Ah, that's right, Koharu-san.

71
00:04:15,488 --> 00:04:19,993
It was hectic for a while, but I've calmed down ➡

72
00:04:19,993 --> 00:04:23,493
Can we meet somewhere slowly?

73
00:04:25,999 --> 00:04:30,003
Dede... then...!

74
00:04:30,003 --> 00:04:34,503
Would you like to go on a date on February 14th?

75
00:04:41,514 --> 00:05:01,534
♬～

76
00:05:01,534 --> 00:05:21,487
♬～

77
00:05:21,487 --> 00:05:37,003
♬～

78
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:42,003
♬～

79
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:47,013
``What should I do with the Valentine chocolates I give to Kurosaki-san? 》

80
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:49,015
《Handmade is confirmed➡

81
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:52,018
Wouldn't it be better to make it with bitter chocolate that's not too sweet? 》

82
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:55,018
(Yao) Koharu-chan, I'm setting out the freshly made rice balls.

83
00:05:57,023 --> 00:06:02,028
《Is the shape really a heart? But that's embarrassing...》

84
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:03,963
《No, but I'm going to confess➡

85
00:06:03,963 --> 00:06:05,965
This is not the time to be shy! 》

86
00:06:05,965 --> 00:06:08,468
Dare to make a heart-shaped chocolate cake!?

87
00:06:08,468 --> 00:06:09,969
Huh?

88
00:06:09,969 --> 00:06:12,472
Valentine's Day is coming soon.

89
00:06:12,472 --> 00:06:13,973
Yuio-san...!

90
00:06:13,973 --> 00:06:16,476
It's okay, you look like a high school student.

91
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:20,480
But I can't believe you're thinking so hard➡

92
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,482
CURO is happy.

93
00:06:22,482 --> 00:06:24,484
Huh... why...｡

94
00:06:24,484 --> 00:06:27,487
I thought maybe that was the case.

95
00:06:27,487 --> 00:06:29,487
Is that really the case?

96
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:32,992
No... well... uh...➡

97
00:06:32,992 --> 00:06:35,995
I'm indebted to you for all sorts of things, so...

98
00:06:35,995 --> 00:06:39,999
It's okay, I won't tell anyone.

99
00:06:39,999 --> 00:06:43,503
I think you'll be happy with that.

100
00:06:43,503 --> 00:06:47,507
I don't think that person has ever received chocolate.

101
00:06:47,507 --> 00:06:49,007
picture?

102
00:06:51,010 --> 00:06:53,510
Hehe, somehow.

103
00:06:57,016 --> 00:07:00,016
《It's my first time trying favorite chocolate, so let's do our best! 》

104
00:07:07,961 --> 00:07:12,966
♬～

105
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:14,966
《10 minutes ago...》

106
00:07:16,970 --> 00:07:18,972
《Can you have a good conversation? 》

107
00:07:18,972 --> 00:07:22,475
《I feel like my heart is pounding just by looking at your face again...》

108
00:07:22,475 --> 00:07:24,475
Mr. Koharu.

109
00:07:26,479 --> 00:07:28,979
Thank you very much for the invitation.

110
00:07:30,984 --> 00:07:33,984
《I don't remember inviting koalas》

111
00:07:35,488 --> 00:07:37,490
Are you Kurosaki-san?

112
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:38,992
yes.

113
00:07:38,992 --> 00:07:40,994
Why are you dressed like that?

114
00:07:40,994 --> 00:07:43,997
I caused a lot of noise and inconvenienced you several times➡

115
00:07:43,997 --> 00:07:46,499
I decided to hide my face.

116
00:07:46,499 --> 00:07:50,003
I'm glad you care, but...

117
00:07:50,003 --> 00:07:52,005
On the contrary, it stands out.

118
00:07:52,005 --> 00:07:54,007
picture….

119
00:07:54,007 --> 00:07:58,007
(Noisy) Koala…｡

120
00:08:00,513 --> 00:08:02,515
Why not hide it with a scarf?

121
00:08:02,515 --> 00:08:05,515
Ah, I see, I will do that.

122
00:08:08,521 --> 00:08:12,525
《But thanks to the koala, my excitement may have subsided.》

123
00:08:12,525 --> 00:08:14,525
"thank you! koala"

124
00:08:16,529 --> 00:08:18,531
Shall we come?

125
00:08:18,531 --> 00:08:20,031
yes!

126
00:08:23,036 --> 00:08:25,038
Ah.

127
00:08:25,038 --> 00:08:27,540
Ah, sorry.

128
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:30,543
When we go on a date, we hold hands➡

129
00:08:30,543 --> 00:08:32,543
Because it was written in the book.

130
00:08:35,982 --> 00:08:38,482
No, it's not.

131
00:08:40,487 --> 00:08:43,487
I want to connect with Koharu-san.

132
00:08:46,493 --> 00:08:49,993
I... I was just surprised by how sudden it was.

133
00:08:51,498 --> 00:08:54,498
It's not bad.

134
00:08:58,505 --> 00:09:00,505
good.

135
00:09:03,009 --> 00:09:05,009
Shall we go?

136
00:09:11,017 --> 00:09:13,520
What should we do first?

137
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:17,023
Sorry, this is my first time playing at an amusement park.

138
00:09:17,023 --> 00:09:20,527
Well, that's right...

139
00:09:20,527 --> 00:09:24,030
Ah, why not try wearing something like that?

140
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:28,530
Ah, ``When you enter the village, obey the village.''

141
00:09:34,974 --> 00:09:39,979
《As expected, there are so many Valentine couples...》

142
00:09:39,979 --> 00:09:44,979
《Maybe we see it that way too? 》

143
00:09:49,489 --> 00:09:52,492
I'll do this.

144
00:09:52,492 --> 00:09:54,992
《Yes, it's cute~! 》

145
00:09:56,996 --> 00:09:58,998
Oh… it suits you!

146
00:09:58,998 --> 00:10:01,998
What should I do...

147
00:10:08,007 --> 00:10:10,007
Mr. Koharu.

148
00:10:12,011 --> 00:10:14,013
《What... what? 》

149
00:10:14,013 --> 00:10:15,515
(encourage)

150
00:10:15,515 --> 00:10:18,515
Would you like to match with me?

151
00:10:24,023 --> 00:10:25,523
Look.

152
00:10:27,527 --> 00:10:30,027
It's very cute.

153
00:10:31,531 --> 00:10:35,468
``Am I really okay like this? 》

154
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,971
《No, for confession➡

155
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:40,971
I can withstand Nekozaki-san's pounding! 》

156
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:43,977
((Cat meows))

157
00:10:43,977 --> 00:11:00,994
♬～

158
00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:05,494
It's a kangaroo! Eh, it's my first time seeing it!

159
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:12,005
There are so many types of owls.

160
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:14,007
That's right. I didn't know.

161
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:16,009
That glasses owl➡

162
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:19,012
Doesn't it look a bit like Kiriya-san?

163
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:22,015
They look similar. Oh, really?

164
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:26,019
I think it's better not to tell him. Eh, why?

165
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:28,021
I'm getting angry again.

166
00:11:28,021 --> 00:11:30,523
But isn't that owl cool?

167
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:32,523
That's a compliment.

168
00:11:33,526 --> 00:11:36,963
This... is it like this? Ah, just a little more here...

169
00:11:36,963 --> 00:11:38,464
a….

170
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:40,964
(Animal sounds) (2 people) Ah...｡

171
00:11:45,972 --> 00:11:48,972
(encourage)

172
00:11:54,981 --> 00:11:57,984
I ate it for the first time and it was delicious.

173
00:11:57,984 --> 00:11:59,984
It was good.

174
00:12:00,987 --> 00:12:04,991
Ah, would you like to try the chocolate flavor?

175
00:12:04,991 --> 00:12:06,993
Eh, no...

176
00:12:06,993 --> 00:12:08,993
It's very delicious.

177
00:12:10,997 --> 00:12:13,497
Well, just one sip.

178
00:12:17,003 --> 00:12:21,507
(encourage)

179
00:12:21,507 --> 00:12:24,510
《I'm enduring, I'm enduring! 》

180
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:26,510
Is it delicious?

181
00:12:29,515 --> 00:12:33,515
Ah, what about that next?

182
00:12:34,954 --> 00:12:37,457
(Screams of passengers)

183
00:12:37,457 --> 00:12:42,457
I've never had the experience of screaming.

184
00:12:43,463 --> 00:12:46,966
“It really stimulates the heart.”

185
00:12:46,966 --> 00:12:49,969
《But if Mr. Kurosaki wants to ride》

186
00:12:49,969 --> 00:12:51,471
Let's ride!

187
00:12:51,471 --> 00:12:52,971
yes!

188
00:12:59,979 --> 00:13:03,479
Wow! Ah~!

189
00:13:08,488 --> 00:13:11,491
Thrill and excitement...

190
00:13:11,491 --> 00:13:14,494
This is a hair-raising feeling...!

191
00:13:14,494 --> 00:13:16,496
Souke...?

192
00:13:16,496 --> 00:13:20,996
Ah... it's a condition where the hair all over your body stands on end.

193
00:13:22,502 --> 00:13:26,002
《It wasn't a big deal.》

194
00:13:28,007 --> 00:13:31,007
Koharu-san has hair on her face.

195
00:13:33,012 --> 00:13:38,951
(encourage)

196
00:13:38,951 --> 00:13:40,953
《Maybe it's impossible~》

197
00:13:40,953 --> 00:13:42,953
Ah... Ah, Koharu-san!

198
00:13:45,958 --> 00:13:48,961
Please. Thank you.

199
00:13:48,961 --> 00:13:51,964
I'm sorry for making you tired.

200
00:13:51,964 --> 00:13:55,468
No, I'm having fun too.

201
00:13:55,468 --> 00:13:57,468
I'll enjoy having this.

202
00:14:01,474 --> 00:14:03,474
It's delicious!

203
00:14:06,979 --> 00:14:10,983
Come to think of it, I remembered this when I bought this➡

204
00:14:10,983 --> 00:14:13,486
Me This amusement park➡

205
00:14:13,486 --> 00:14:16,489
I came here once on a field trip with my junior high school.

206
00:14:16,489 --> 00:14:18,991
Was that so? yes.

207
00:14:18,991 --> 00:14:21,994
At that time, I bought coffee by myself ➡

208
00:14:21,994 --> 00:14:23,996
Spend your time reading books.

209
00:14:23,996 --> 00:14:30,002
(Sounds of students talking)

210
00:14:30,002 --> 00:14:33,002
It wasn't that I didn't feel lonely.

211
00:14:34,941 --> 00:14:38,945
But... if I were there➡

212
00:14:38,945 --> 00:14:41,945
It often destroys the fun atmosphere.

213
00:14:43,449 --> 00:14:49,956
At home, at school, or anywhere in the world➡

214
00:14:49,956 --> 00:14:52,956
I was an unnecessary piece.

215
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:59,465
But I can't believe I'm with Koharu-san today➡

216
00:14:59,465 --> 00:15:01,965
Happy like a dream.

217
00:15:04,470 --> 00:15:08,470
If this is a dream, please don't wake up.

218
00:15:11,978 --> 00:15:14,478
It's not a dream.

219
00:15:16,482 --> 00:15:21,482
I'm right next to Kurosaki-san.

220
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:25,990
Mr. Kurosaki.

221
00:15:28,995 --> 00:15:32,498
Could you please take this?

222
00:15:32,498 --> 00:15:36,436
This... could this be...?

223
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:39,439
Valentine's chocolate.

224
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:43,443
I made this with all my heart for Kurosaki-san.

225
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:45,443
For me?

226
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:49,949
That means...➡

227
00:15:49,949 --> 00:15:51,951
It's chocolate for those who are interested!

228
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:53,953
picture? Ah...｡

229
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:56,956
In the world, there are chocolates such as duty chocolate, friend chocolate, and honmei chocolate➡

230
00:15:56,956 --> 00:16:00,960
I read in a book that there are different types.

231
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:06,466
Sigh... this is going to be a family heirloom... no, I'll have it right away.

232
00:16:06,466 --> 00:16:07,967
No.

233
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:09,467
picture?

234
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:13,971
Mr. Kurosaki...

235
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:19,476
This is the person I like.

236
00:16:22,482 --> 00:16:25,982
Eh... that's...

237
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,989
⚟I've seen that guy somewhere! ⚞

238
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:32,992
Huh? Seriously? Ku... Kurosaki-san, let's go!

239
00:16:32,992 --> 00:16:36,892
That's right! It's really cool though!

240
00:16:43,936 --> 00:16:47,439
Ha ha…｡ Haa…｡

241
00:16:47,439 --> 00:16:54,339
Ha ha ha ha...

242
00:16:57,883 --> 00:17:02,383
Koharu-san... What you said earlier...

243
00:17:04,890 --> 00:17:09,895
I didn't mean to say it in a place like that.

244
00:17:09,895 --> 00:17:14,900
Kurosaki-san was careful.

245
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:20,400
But I can't stop feeling.

246
00:17:23,408 --> 00:17:24,910
Sigh…｡

247
00:17:24,910 --> 00:17:30,916
Honestly, I've been causing Kurosaki-san a lot of trouble.

248
00:17:30,916 --> 00:17:33,416
What are you doing...

249
00:17:38,924 --> 00:17:42,424
It's okay, please calm down.

250
00:17:44,429 --> 00:17:46,932
The meaning of the word “person I like”➡

251
00:17:46,932 --> 00:17:49,935
If it's what I think ➡

252
00:17:49,935 --> 00:17:53,872
No matter when, where, or in front of whom it is said➡

253
00:17:53,872 --> 00:17:56,872
I don't think it would be a nuisance.

254
00:17:58,377 --> 00:18:02,381
But... my existence➡

255
00:18:02,381 --> 00:18:05,881
What if I pull Kurosaki-san's leg...

256
00:18:07,386 --> 00:18:12,391
As I mentioned before, Koharu-san’s existence is➡

257
00:18:12,391 --> 00:18:16,891
Please make my heart light and strong.

258
00:18:18,897 --> 00:18:23,902
Even if difficulties come, when I think of Koharu-san➡

259
00:18:23,902 --> 00:18:26,902
You can overcome anything.

260
00:18:30,909 --> 00:18:35,909
Mr. Kurosaki was... that kind of person.

261
00:18:38,417 --> 00:18:42,921
It's embarrassingly fast forward.

262
00:18:42,921 --> 00:18:45,924
It's a little off.

